snippet.textDisplay: Thanks professor, love your show! Question: why did you attribute more reliability to the second test? If they were both as reliable as each other, you must conclude that the second test was a false negative (so would need a third test to break the tie), or that you could well have been an asymptomatic carrier. Stay safe, keep educating the world!
